block.l: Pick a number between 1 and 94 to use as a cypher key
Type "e" to encrypt and send a message. Type "d" to decrypt a message.

block.comment: We are subtracting 31 because the unicode for the first "printable character" is 32. That way, our list of printable characters starts at 1 (32-31=1).

list.l: A window will open where you can send in your message:

custom-block.s: submit %txt with key %n to Google Forms

block.comment: You'll have to put all of these blocks together to build a message decoder.
We have to add 31 back in because we subracted it when we encoded the messages.

block-definition.s: submit %'msg' with key %'key' to Google Forms
